%pyspark
'''
function for calulating the taxi trip duration 
'''
import time
from datetime import datetime

def timeCal(start,end):
    struct_time = time.strptime(start, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
    struct_time1 = time.strptime(end, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")

    dt = datetime.fromtimestamp(time.mktime(struct_time))
    dt1 = datetime.fromtimestamp(time.mktime(struct_time1))

    result=dt1-dt
    return result.seconds

def monthDataFilter(data,month):
    theMonth = int(data[0:2])
    if theMonth == month:
        return True
    else:
        return False

Analysis the bike and the taxi data

# List for saving the statistical result

# We got bike data from 07/2013 - 06/2016
for year in range(2013,2017):
    for month in range(1,13):
        if (year == 2013 and month < 7) or (year == 2016 and month > 6):
            continue

                monthS = '0'+str(month)

                monthS = str(month)
            
                
            bikeFilePath = "/user/lc3442/finalProject/cityBike/"+str(year)+monthS+"-citibike-tripdata.csv"
            taxiFilePath = "/user/lc3442/finalProject/yellow/"+str(year)+"/yellow_tripdata_"+str(year)+"-"+monthS+".csv"
            print taxiFilePath
            
            #handle different dataset structure for taxi data
            bikeDF = sqlContext.read.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").option("header", "false").schema(bikeSchema).load(bikeFilePath)
            if year<2015:
                taxiDF = sqlContext.read.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").option("header", "false").schema(yellowSchema2).load(taxiFilePath)

            bikeDF.show()
            taxiDF.show()
            bikeDF.registerTempTable("bikeTrip")
            
            #Group bike data by start location and end location, and only select trips with more than 5 minutes. Get top 20 route results.  
            bikeGroupDF = sqlContext.sql("Select start_station_name,end_station_name,first(start_station_latitude),first(start_station_longitude),first(end_station_latitude),first(end_station_longitude),count(tripduration) As totaltrips ,AVG(tripduration) as avgtriptime From bikeTrip Where tripduration>300 Group By start_station_name , end_station_name Order By totaltrips DESC LIMIT 20")
            
            #From the taxi data, for each route in top 20 bike route, select the data with nearby pickup and dropoff location, count the datas, we define the nearby range as a square with 600m length of sides.
            for row in bikeGroupDF.collect():
                slat = row["_c2"]
                slon = row["_c3"]
                elat = row["_c4"]
                elon = row["_c5"]
                print "Start: "+row["start_station_name"] + " End: "+ row["end_station_name"] + "***" + str(year)+monthS
                nearTaxiData = taxiDF.where((col("Pickup_longitude") > slon-0.0036) & (col("Pickup_longitude") < slon+0.0036) & (col("Pickup_latitude") > slat-0.0027) & (col("Pickup_latitude") < slat+0.0027) & (col("Dropoff_longitude") > elon-0.0036) & (col("Pickup_longitude") < elon+0.0036) & (col("Dropoff_latitude") > elat-0.0027) & (col("Dropoff_latitude") < elat+0.0027))
                
                #Calculate the avg taxi trip duration
                totaltimes=0
                for taxirow in nearTaxiData.collect():
                    singletime = timeCal(taxirow["Pickup_datetime"],taxirow["Dropoff_datetime"])
                    totaltimes += singletime
                    
                if nearTaxiData.count() != 0:
                    avgtaxitriptime = totaltimes/nearTaxiData.count()
                else:
                    avgtaxitriptime = 0
                
                singleData = (str(year)+monthS,row["start_station_name"],row["end_station_name"],row["totaltrips"],nearTaxiData.count(),row["avgtriptime"],avgtaxitriptime,row["_c2"],row["_c3"],row["_c4"],row["_c5"])
                allData.append(singleData)
                print singleData

#save the result to HDFS
allDataRdd = sc.parallelize(allData)
allDataDF = sqlContext.createDataFrame(allDataRdd, ['time','start_station_name',"end_station_name","total_bike_trips","total_taxi_trips","avg_bike_trip_duration","avg_taxi_trip_duration","start_lat","start_lon","end_lat","end_lon"])
allDataDF.write.format('com.databricks.spark.csv').save('/user/lc3442/finalProject/BikeDataAnalysisOutput1.csv')
